10.1.2 C++ Semantic Values
--------------------------

Bison supports two different means to handle semantic values in C++.
One is alike the C interface, and relies on unions (*note C++ Unions::).
As C++ practitioners know, unions are inconvenient in C++, therefore
another approach is provided, based on variants (*note C++ Variants::).

* Menu:

* C++ Unions::             Semantic values cannot be objects
* C++ Variants::           Using objects as semantic values


